Every enemy unit on the battlefield is struck by one of the following spell effects, selected at random:
* No effect;
* {{Life|link = Healing}};
* {{Chaos|link = Chaos Channels}};
* {{Chaos|link = Warp Creature}};
* {{Chaos|link = Fire Bolt}} (strength {{Ranged|magic|15}});
* {{Chaos|link = Warp Lightning}};
* {{Chaos|link = Doom Bolt}};
* {{Chaos|link = Disintegrate}}.

Every enemy unit on the battlefield suffers the following penalties:
* '''-1''' to all [[Attack Strength]]s (except for {{Ranged|magic|Spell Damage}});
* {{Defense|-1}} [[Defense]];
* {{Save|-2}} [[Resistance]].

All friendly units on the battlefield receive the following bonuses:
* {{Melee|+2 Melee Strength}};
* {{Defense|+2 Defense}};
* {{To Hit|+10% To Hit}};
* {{To Block|+10% To Block}};
* {{Resist|+3 Resistance}}.
All enemy units on the battlefield receive a {{To Hit|-10% To Hit}} penalty to their [[Melee Attack]]s.

All friendly [[Normal Unit]]s and [[Hero]]es receive the following bonuses:
* {{Melee|Normal|+1}}
* {{Ranged|Bow|+1}}
* {{Thrown|+1}} (if the unit possesses a Thrown Attack at all)
* The unit now has a {{Melee|Magic|Magical Melee Attack}} if it did not already have a better one.

All friendly units on the battlefield receive the following bonuses:
* {{To Hit|+10% To Hit}};
* {{To Block|+10% To Block}};
* {{Resist|+1 Resistance}}.
All enemy units on the battlefield receive a {{To Hit|-10% To Hit}} penalty to their [[Melee Attack]]s.

Target [[Normal Unit]], [[Hero]] or [[Undead]] receives the following bonuses:
* {{Melee|Normal|+2}} [[Attack Strength#Melee Strength|Melee Strength]];
* {{Ranged|General|+1}} Ranged [[Attack Strength]] (including short-range, if applicable);
* {{Defense|+1}} [[Defense]];
* {{Resist|+1}} [[Resistance]];
* {{Hits|+1}} [[Hit Points]] per {{Figure|figure}}.

If a Normal Unit or Hero is targeted by this spell, they become Undead permanently.

Target [[Normal Unit]] or [[Hero]] is now considered to be a [[Fantastic Unit]] from the {{Chaos|Chaos Realm}}.

In addition, the unit permanently receives ''one'' of the following bonuses:
* {{Defense|+6}} *
* {{Breath|Fire|2}}
* {{Movement|Air|2}}

A unit may only be targeted by [[Chaos Channels]] once. The effect is permanent and cannot be dispelled.

The enchanted unit gets the following bonuses:
* {{Melee|Normal|+2}}
* {{Ranged|Bow|+2}}
* {{Thrown|+2}} (if the unit possesses a [[Thrown Attack]])
* Ignore [[Weapon Immunity]]

Target unit receives the following bonuses:
* {{Melee|Normal|+3 Melee Strength}};
* {{Resist|+3 Resistance}};
* {{Hits|+3 Hits}} per {{Figure|figure}};
* {{Ranged|Bow|+3}}, {{Ranged|Rock|+3}} or {{Thrown|+3}} (if applicable).

Every unit (in the entire game) associated with the {{Chaos|link = Chaos|Chaos Realm}} receives the following bonuses:
* {{Melee|Normal|+2}}
* {{Ranged|Bow|+2}} / {{Ranged|Rock|+2}} / {{Ranged|Magic|+2}}
* {{Breath|Fire|+2}} / {{Thrown|+2}} / [[File:Ability_DoomGaze.png|16px|link=Doom Gaze]]&nbsp;<span style="color:white;">'''+2'''</span>
However, each bonus only applies to units already possessing the relevant [[Attack Type]].

The target [[Town]] suffers the following effects, unless protected by {{Life|link = Consecration}} or {{Sorcery|link = Spell Ward|Chaos Ward}}:
*Each [[Town Building]] has a 50% chance to be destroyed;
*Every 1000 residents above the first have a 50% chance of being slain;
*Every tile in a 5×5 area centered on the Town has a 50% chance of becoming [[Corruption|Corrupted]].
*Every garrisoned unit is struck with a strength {{Ranged|magic|10}} [[Doom Damage]] attack;
*If the target is an [[Outpost]], it is removed from the map.

